{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dcd5b0cb-d268-41cf-9925-97eecda8c6f0","content":"Update these files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. After updating**, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` NuGet packages in your `.csproj` — bump those to their `11.x` versions. Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for anything that affects your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"966e7757-36e3-4254-a4be-5d8b5c9e6803","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":300},"id":"89088afe-39b6-4b85-809d-60dba8f029f7","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:02:02.393Z","parentId":"77d2e6e5-0546-46bf-b55b-e90add6ec463"}
